12/07/2005
LJUBLJANA, Slovenia -- Last week's meeting of representatives of the former Yugoslav countries resulted in an agreement on the distribution of assets, according to the negotiators. Speaking Monday (11 July), Serbia-Montenegro's chief negotiator, Veroljub Dugalic, said foreign reserves worth $220m were divided. The countries also reached a preliminary agreement on the division of obligations arising from guarantees extended by the army council, which used to operate within the former central bank. (Nezavisne Novine, Glas Javnosti - 12/07/05; National Bank of Serbia Web site, RTS, Tanjug - 11/07/05)
